# Matchday Masters 26 - System Architecture

## Core Game Systems

### 1. Player System
- PlayerData: Core player attributes
- PlayerStats: Performance metrics (pace, shooting, passing, etc)
- PlayerProgression: XP, level, skill growth
- CustomPlayer: Player creation engine

### 2. Team System
- TeamData: Team info, squad roster
- Formations: Formation presets (4-3-3, 4-2-4, etc)
- Tactics: In-match tactics (aggressive, defensive, balanced)
- Squad: Team roster management

### 3. Match System
- MatchEngine: Core game loop
- Physics: Ball physics, player movement
- AI: AI opponent behavior
- Events: Match events (goals, fouls, injuries)

### 4. Career System
- PlayerCareer: Individual player progression
- ManagerCareer: Manager/team progression
- Progression: Seasonal progression
- Objectives: Career objectives & milestones

### 5. Multiplayer System
- NetworkManager: Connection handling
- Matchmaking: Player matching
- Leaderboards: Rank tracking
- Synchronization: Game state sync

### 6. UI System
- MenuController: Main menu navigation
- HUD: In-match HUD
- Career UI: Career mode interface
- Customization UI: Player/team creation

### 7. Data Management
- DataManager: Persistent data
- ConfigManager: Game configuration
- LocalDatabase: Offline data
- CloudDatabase: Online progression

## Class Hierarchy

GameManager (Singleton)
├── PlayerManager
├── TeamManager
├── MatchManager
├── CareerManager
├── MultiplayerManager
└── UIManager

## Data Flow

MenuScene -> PlayerCreation -> TeamSelection -> Match -> CareerUpdate -> LeaderboardUpdate

## Dependencies

- Unity 2022 LTS+
- Netcode for GameObjects (multiplayer)
- PlayFab SDK (cloud)
- TextMesh Pro (UI)